It&#8217;s alleged he beat the child and burnt her with a cigarette before sexually assaulting the two-year-old girl. CAPE TOWN - A Malmesbury man has been arrested in connection with the rape of a two-year-old girl.It s alleged he beat the child and burnt her with a cigarette before sexually assaulting her over the weekend.The police's Noloyiso Rwexana says the 24-year-old has been charged with attempted murder and rape. The man was arrested on the charge of murder and attempted rape after the incident which occurred on 6 November. The victim was taken to hospital for treatment. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)